The obvious solution is to use a Web Worker,<p><pre><code>  var code = &quot;onmessage = function (evt) {evt.data.sort(); postMessage(evt.data)}&quot;;

  function asyncSort(data, cb) {
    var worker = new Worker(URL.createObjectURL(new Blob([code])));
    worker.onmessage = function (evt) { cb(evt.data); };
    worker.postMessage(data);
  }
</code></pre>
Example,<p><pre><code>  asyncSort([3, 2, 1], function (res) { console.log(res); });
</code></pre>
Prints,<p><pre><code>  &quot;[1, 2, 3]&quot;</code></pre>

